Prodoxus mapimiensis is a moth of the family Prodoxidae. It is found in Mexico in the Chihuahuan Desert, from Saltillo-Torre north to the Big Bend region of western Texas, United States.
The wingspan is 7.3-10.9 mm for males and 8.8â€“12 mm for females. The forewings are usually white. The hindwings are white with a light gray apex. Adults are on wing from March to April.
The larvae feed on Yucca carnerosana, Yucca linearifolia, Yucca filifera and Yucca treculeana. They feed superficially inside the flowering stalk of their host plant. The larva can diapause for at least three years before pupation and emergence.